curly impersonator david knight, an iron worker from palmyra, n.y., tweaked ears but generally restrained himself from head-knocking, eye-poking and face-slapping. those were some of the slapstick hallmarks of the trio that made more than 190 short films and about 50 feature-length films until the '60s
