the only tv we have is in my office, and i don't expect it to be on most of the day,'' ms. hardt said. ``we'll probably just catch it like everybody else when we go home at night.''
mrs. mofford has told department heads not to watch the trial and her department of administration director has instructed state employees not to watch it during work hours, ms. hardt said
mrs. mofford, a democrat elected as secretary of state, became acting governor when the house impeached mecham, the elected republican governor, on charges he illegally concealed a $350,000 campaign loan, misused $80,000 in state money and obstructed justice
mecham, who says he is innocent, also faces a recall election in may and a criminal trial next month on six felony charges stemming from the campaign loan
mrs. mofford would become governor should mecham be convicted at either trial. should mecham lose the recall, the opponent who received the most votes would become governor
