the pedstrians were standing on the sidewalk waiting for a light to change, police investigator j.m. smith said
when we first arrived here, one of the victims was under the cab,'' police officer j.a. miller said. ``myself and a couple of citizens lifted the cab off her, and pulled her out.''
the 29-year-old driver, whose name was not released, was unable to explain what happened, and was taken to ben taub hospital for treatment, smith said. charges might be filed following further investigation
juanita barrett, 42, was listed in good condition, while gertrudis abdel-khaliq, 37, was listed in guarded condition at hermann hospital, a spokeswoman said. anna hornac 66, was listed in stable condition at st. luke's hospital, a spokeswoman said
