pedro concepcion padilla, 35, of el paso was arrested and charged with attempted sexual assault after miss scoggins, in town to serve as co-host of the miss usa pageant, was attacked in a hotel elevator thursday night
the assailant tore miss scoggins' clothes and pushed her into the back of the elevator. she fought the man off and padilla was detained by hotel guests and security before police arrived and arrested him
romero set $100 bail on the third-degree felony; prosecutors normally ask for $15,000 bail in similar cases. the decision drew strong criticism from miss scoggins, best known as for her role as monica colby in the television show ``the colbys.''
police are investigating ``the actions of the parties involved in setting the bond,'' grijalva said
we received information over the weekend that there may have been collusion between the subjects involved,'' he said. ``we may be looking into some type of misconduct charges.''
grijalva would not elaborate on who else is being investigated. padilla was represented by lawyer jose montes
padilla, who had given police an alias and a false address, surrendered to police saturday after district judge brunson moore issued a new warrant that carried a $100,000 bail. padilla posted the required 15 percent of that amount and is free
