there was no asking price for the building, located at sixth avenue and 53rd street near the rockefeller center complex, said harvey mccormick, a penney spokesman
the entire structure will be left vacant by the move, which began in december and is expected to be completed by the end of june, mccormick said
more than 1,200 of penney's 2,200 management employees were expected to ultimately move with the company to texas, the spokesman said. a ``very small percentage'' of 1,600 non-management workers, who include secretaries and clerical workers, also were transferring, he said
steel production rose to 2.002 million tons in the week ended feb. 27, an increase of 3.1 percent from the previous week's 1.942 million tons, the american iron and steel institute reported monday
the industry's production amounted to 93.2 percent of capacity during the week, compared with 90.4 percent in the previous week
estimated figures for the year to date showed production at 15.798 million net tons, an increase of 39.7 percent from the 11.308 million net tons in the previous year. the steel operations of usx corp., the nation's largest steel producer, were shut down by a strike during the first month of 1987
production so far this year used 88.8 percent of capacity, compared with 64.1 percent a year earlier
net tonnage by district for the week ended feb. 27: northeast coast, 285,000; pittsburgh, 208,000; youngstown, 125,000; lake erie, 165,000; detroit, 164,000; chicago, 539,000; midwest, 195,000; southern, 223,000; and western, 98,000
